casebody.data:
STATE EX REL. Tyrone D. JOHNSON
v.
STATE of Louisiana No. 2017-KH-2105 Supreme Court of Louisiana. January 14, 2019

ON SUPERVISORY WRITS TO THE FIFTH JUDICIAL DISTRICT COURT, PARISH OF RICHLAND

PER CURIAM:

Writ granted; case remanded to the district court. The district court is ordered to grant relator an out-of-time appeal and appoint counsel to prosecute it. State v. Counterman , 475 So.2d 336 , 340 (La. 1985).
